Medical doctors in India (and most other countries) rely on paper prescriptions as the primary health record even today, despite its inherent deficiencies (disjointed patient datasets, lack of continuity of care, etc.). This results in an expensive and inefficient process, directly having a negative impact on overall health care. On the other hand, current techniques around EMR takes the doctors' eyes away from the patient, to type patient data via a computer screen. Here is a novel approach.

Online Medical Records eXchange (OmRx) is a platform exclusively for doctors, to digitize paper prescriptions, test reports, referral letters, and many more, resulting in anytime anywhere access of patient data to health professionals.

Key features of the OmRx health technology platform are:
- digitize paper based patient data for a 360 degree view;
- delegate digitization process;
- easy to learn; start using it in minutes;
- complete access to patient data during its lifecycle;
- secure data to prevent unauthorized access;

The core benefits of the above platform are:
- patient data at your finger tips anytime, anywhere;
- almost no change to your existing process;
- holistic decision making to improve the overall patient care;
- maintain eye contact for that long term patient-doctor relationship, critical for overall heathcare experience.

Finally, no health data is stored on the OmRx app, thereby preventing unauthorized access or compromising patient privacy.
